                     <title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Ḥibur be-diḳduḳ ῾ivri</title>
                     
                     
                     
                     <title xml:lang="he">חבור בדקדוק עברי</title>
                     
                     
                     
                     <note>
                        
                        
                        
                        <p>The work is divided into three parts: "Compendious and easy Rules to Read and pronounce by Accent the Hebrew Tongue - both with Points, and without"; "Dr. Rudds short Instructions but very plain and easy to Read Hebrew and pronounce in truely by Accent" (folio 26v); "Of the Hebrew Roots, or Primitive words. Rules - To finde out the Root or Theme, and how to use a Dictionary" (folio 33r). At the end: "Finis. 1714".</p>
                        
                        
                        
                        <p>A table of the Hebrew verbal forms, with paradigms, is appended, headed as follows: "A Paradigme of the Eight Orders of Verbs."</p>
                     
                     
                     
                     </note>
                  
                  
                  
